cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as temporal expression identification and normalization. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses conditional random fields and rule-based temporal normalizer for the identification and normalization tasks. Additionally, it may fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the extraction of temporal information from text, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are commonly used in natural language processing tasks.
